-- Insurer Travelers profit soars as disaster losses slide
-- 
-- Tue Jan 21, 2014 07:08AM EST
-- None



Jan 21 (Reuters) - U.S. insurer Travelers Cos Inc <TRV.N> posted a more than three-fold rise in fourth-quarter profit as the company earned higher premiums and disaster losses declined.

The company's net income rose to $988 million, or $2.70 per share, for the quarter ended Dec. 31, from $304 million, or 78 cents per share, a year earlier. Operating earnings were $2.68 per share. [ID:nBw9Z5JRZa] Total revenue rose 4 percent to $6.74 billion.